{#
  hx-copy-button — Drupal Twig Template
  ======================================

  Server-renders the hx-copy-button custom element with correct attributes.
  The Web Component self-registers; no Drupal behavior is required for basic
  clipboard copy functionality.

  Parameters:
    value            (string)  Required. The text to write to the clipboard.
                               IMPORTANT: Use the `|e('html_attr')` filter (not `|raw`)
                               to safely pass values that may contain special characters.
                               The component reads the attribute as a raw string, so
                               Twig's default autoescape will HTML-encode characters
                               like & → &amp;. Use `|e('html_attr')` to HTML-attribute-
                               encode while preserving the intended raw value in the DOM.
                               Example: value="{{ node.field_mrn.value|e('html_attr') }}"
    label            (string)  Optional. Accessible label for the button (aria-label +
                               title). Defaults to 'Copy to clipboard'. Always provide
                               a label that describes WHAT is being copied, e.g.
                               "Copy patient MRN" for clinical context.
    feedback_duration (number) Optional. Duration in milliseconds to display the
                               success state. Defaults to 2000. Minimum: 300 ms.
                               Maps to the `feedback-duration` attribute.
    size             (string)  Optional. One of: sm | md | lg. Defaults to 'md'.
                               Maps to the `hx-size` attribute.
    disabled         (bool)    Optional. Renders the button in a disabled,
                               non-interactive state. Defaults to false.
    attributes       (object)  Optional. Additional HTML attributes to spread
                               onto the element (e.g., data-* attributes).

  Usage examples:

    Basic copy button (icon-only, accessible via label):
      {% include 'hx-copy-button.twig' with {
        value: 'Hello world',
        label: 'Copy to clipboard',
      } %}

    Copy patient MRN in a clinical data row:
      {% include 'hx-copy-button.twig' with {
        value: node.field_patient_mrn.value,
        label: 'Copy patient MRN',
        size: 'sm',
        feedback_duration: 3000,
      } %}

    Disabled copy button (e.g., clipboard unavailable or field empty):
      {% include 'hx-copy-button.twig' with {
        value: '',
        label: 'Copy unavailable',
        disabled: true,
      } %}

  Drupal behavior for advanced JS integration:
    The element dispatches two CustomEvents (bubbles: true, composed: true):
      hx-copy       — After successful clipboard write. detail: { value }
      hx-copy-error — On clipboard failure. detail: { value, error }

    Example Drupal behavior:
      (function (Drupal) {
        Drupal.behaviors.helixCopyButton = {
          attach: function (context) {
            context.querySelectorAll('hx-copy-button').forEach((el) => {
              el.addEventListener('hx-copy', (e) => {
                // Optional: analytics, audit log, toast notification, etc.
                console.log('Copied:', e.detail.value);
              });
              el.addEventListener('hx-copy-error', (e) => {
                // Show fallback UI or error message when clipboard is blocked.
                Drupal.announce(
                  Drupal.t('Copy to clipboard failed. Please copy manually.'),
                  'assertive',
                );
              });
            });
          },
        };
      })(Drupal);

  Note on Twig auto-escaping and special characters:
    Twig's autoescape converts & → &amp;, < → &lt;, " → &quot; etc. when
    interpolating into text content. When setting HTML *attributes* with
    {{ value }}, Twig applies html attribute escaping. The component reads the
    attribute value as a raw DOM string via the `value` property, which means
    the browser will have already decoded HTML entities. This is safe and
    correct: {{ node.field_data.value }} will produce the intended string.
    If you are unsure, always prefer {{ value|e('html_attr') }} for attribute
    values as an explicit safe guard.
#}

<hx-copy-button
  value="{{ value|default('')|e('html_attr') }}"
  {% if label %}label="{{ label|e('html_attr') }}"{% endif %}
  {% if feedback_duration %}feedback-duration="{{ feedback_duration }}"{% endif %}
  hx-size="{{ size|default('md') }}"
  {% if disabled %}disabled{% endif %}
  {% for key, val in attributes|default({}) %}{{ key }}="{{ val|e('html_attr') }}" {% endfor %}
>
  {% block copy_icon %}
    {#
      Provide a copy icon via the copy-icon named slot. Example:
        {% block copy_icon %}
          <svg slot="copy-icon" aria-hidden="true" ...>...</svg>
        {% endblock %}
    #}
  {% endblock %}
  {% block success_icon %}
    {#
      Provide a success/checkmark icon via the success-icon named slot. Example:
        {% block success_icon %}
          <svg slot="success-icon" aria-hidden="true" ...>...</svg>
        {% endblock %}
    #}
  {% endblock %}
  {% block label_text %}{% endblock %}
</hx-copy-button>
